 use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":58,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Rev John I Toldervey was born in 1500, in Oxford, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom. He married Alice Sadlier in 1522, in Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 1 daughter. He died on 18 April 1567, in his hometown, at the age of 67, and was buried in Oxford, Oxfordshire, England."},"et":{"1500–18 April 1567":"1500–18. aprill 1567","1504–1583":"1504–1583","1525–1567":"1525–1567","1553–1630":"1553–1630","1558–Male":"1558–Surnud","1560–Female":"1560–Surnud","1500–1567":"1500–1567","23 Apr 1567":"23. aprill 1567","1583":"1583","1560":"1560","18 April 1567":"18. aprill 1567","1525":"1525","1558":"1558","1567":"1567","1500":"1500","1522":"1522","<1558>":"1558","1630":"1630","1553":"1553","18 Apr 1567":"18. aprill 1567","about 1553":"umbes 1553","1549":"1549","1504":"1504","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, England","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Eng":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1500–18 April 1567":"1500–18. huhtikuuta 1567","1504–1583":"1504–1583","1525–1567":"1525–1567","1553–1630":"1553–1630","1558–Male":"1558–Kuollut","1560–Female":"1560–Kuollut","1500–1567":"1500–1567","23 Apr 1567":"23. huhtikuuta 1567","1583":"1583","1560":"1560","18 April 1567":"18. huhtikuuta 1567","1525":"1525","1558":"1558","1567